TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(2,9,1);
$b1 = random(2,9,1);
$c1 = sqrt($b1/$a1);
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Consider the function \( f(x) = $a1 x + $b1 x ^ { -1 } \).
For this function there are four important intervals:
 \( (-\infty, A] \), \( [A,B) \),\( (B,C) \), and \( [C,\infty) \) where
 \( A \), \(B\) and \( C \) are either critical numbers or points at which \(f(x)\)
is undefined.
$BR
Find \( A \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = -$c1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
and  \( B \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = 0;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
and  \( C \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $c1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));

